title: Grateful Dead Live at Shoreline Amphitheatre on 1987-10-03
description:
Set 1

Hey Pocky Way, Minglewood Blues, Candyman, Addam's Family, When I Paint My Masterpiece, West L.A. Fadeaway, My Brother Esau, Bird Song, The Music Never Stopped

Set 2

Maggie's Farm-> Cumberland Blues, Looks Like Rain, Terrapin Station-> Drums-> Jam-> The Other One-> Stella Blue-> Throwing Stones-> Turn On Your Love Light, E: The Mighty Quinn

Final My Brother Esau, "Addams Family" tuning before "Masterpiece"

reviews.review_text: Parking Lot Miracle This was my most memorable GD show mostly for sentimental reasons. I was pretty high and got lost in the parking lot when someone came up to me and said "you look lost." They gave me a blotter of Red Mars and I somehow made it into the show with my friends. First half of the show is pretty hazy and for a while but Terrapin kicked in and it pulled me back down to earth. I lost my shoes and after the show we sat on the sidewalk for a few hours. I think we were the last to leave the parking lot. It was a sea of glittering broken glass. I walked barefoot across the lot and didnt even get a sliver or cut. Beautiful and weird night for sure
